{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One's communications with others could be observed in IXR, but biometric data could facilitate more subtle invasions.",
    "Researchers in a Stanford class held in VR used biometric data to infer information about group dynamics and relationships between users (Stanford HAI, 2022).",
    "The same could be done by observing an individual's interactions with bystanders not using IXR.",
    "The IXR environment is never fully detached from the physical space within which it is experienced.",
    "Any interactions in the physical space, e.g., words exchanged with a co-worker who enters the office, may also be shared in the IXR environment."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Researchers in a Stanford class held in VR used biometric data to infer information about group dynamics and relationships between users (Stanford HAI, 2022)."
  ]
}